	dprr:hasNoteText "pp. 65-72" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8424> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8424" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 729" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2417> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2417" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Liguria, but sent his troops to the Praetor in Sardinia (Liv. 40.19.8, and 25.7)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2389> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2389" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Macrobius dates this law in the third year after Cato's censorship (184) and in the twenty-second before the Lex Fannia (161)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2388> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2388" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 39.56.4; 40.44.11; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 456f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Aemilius, Elogia, CIL 1\n     .1, pp. 194, 198- Inscr. Ital. 13.3.71b and 81; Val. Max. 7.5.3; Vell. 1.9.3; Auct. Vir. Ill. 56.1. Both Consuls were assigned commands in Liguria and won successes (Liv. 40.1.1 and 5, 16.4, and 17.6-7, and on Aemilius, Plut. Aem. 6.1-3). Baebius returned to Rome to hold the elections (Liv. 40.17.8)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2315> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2315" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected at the end of the year to add colonists to the deserted colonies of Sipontum and Buxentum (Liv. 39.23.3-4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1960> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1960" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Defeated by the Insubres and ordered to Rome by the Consul (Liv. 32.7.5-7; Zon. 9.15)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1931> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1931" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 31.50.3; Didasc. Plaut. Stich. (with C. Terentius)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1846> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1846" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Indicted the Censors for their public quarrel (Liv. 29.37.17; Val. Max. 7.2.6; see 204, Censors). Niccolini places him in 204 (FTP 100), but his action appears to refer to the later part of the Censors' activities. See 204, Tribunes of the Plebs and note 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1806> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1806" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Grueber, CRRBM 1.133, doubts any association of the coins of a M. Baebius Tamphilus with the Baebii of this time (cf. Mommsen, RMW 495; Babelon 1.250ff.) since they are much later, unless the Apollo type may possibly refer to some ancestral connection with the Ludi Apollinares (Grueber, loc. cit., note 4; cf. Babelon 1.254). Niccolini (FTP 100) dates him in 204, but possibly 203 is correct, since his action appears to refer to the later part of the activity of the Censors." .
